  <h1>On a Quest to Eat at the World’s 50 Best Restaurants Before I Turn&nbsp;50</h1>
  <div>
    <p>There is a scene in the movie, Ratatouille, when Anton Ego, the inimitable food critic, takes a bite of the titular dish. He is instantly transported to his childhood. There is something about being in that moment. The rest of the world disappears. I can no longer hear. I can no longer see. All I can do is taste. And it is pure pleasure.</p>

    <p><em>This is the moment I seek.</em></p>

    <p>This journey will take me around the world, to visit 50 of the <a href="https://www.theworlds50best.com">World’s Best Restaurants</a>. I am no food critic. I have no sway. I’m just a guy who enjoys good food and enjoys to travel. </p>

    <p>I have a <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1NPckHqoxjhqoUIzrI2KSzU1AWeettEVEsykZYgUyd9w/edit?usp=sharing">spreadsheet of all the restaurants</a>. Each year, a new list comes out and I update this spreadsheet. What you’ll find on this site is a history of all the places I’ve been. </p>

    <p>Enjoy!</p>
